column27:
my reaction is negative... Here are 18 points why:

1. Forced attempt at humor with Poe Dameraan prank calling the Admiral at the beginning of the movie.

2. Something felt tonally off when they pulled Maz Kanata up on the view port... felt like they were bringing in a marvel character or one of the avengers or something...

3. They killed Supreme Leader Snoke off without any problems and never gave any information about his backstory whatsoever.

4. The overall primary plot of the movie (Snoke\'s capital ships slowly chasing after the resistance ships) is not very interesting.

5. Stupid fucking jokes throughout the movie. Overall tone felt like a poor imitation of Guardians of the Galaxy.

6. Captain Phasma was pushed as a relatively major character but never really got any screen time in either of the movies she appeared in and then she died.

7. They killed Admiral Ackbar and I didn\'t even realize that it happened at first.

8. Luke Skywalker milks a fat alien with 4 breasts and immediately drinks the milk.

9. Leia gets bombed and ripped out of her ship and into the vacuum. After she freezes to death she comes back to life like a space witch and levitates back into the ship.

10. When Kylo Ren and Rey first start telepathically communicating it somehow feels so out of place it was absurd. Admittedly
column28:
it does get better after the first session...

11. Adam Driver has strong chest muscles.

12. Almost the entire middle section of the movie could have been cut out without losing anything. It probably would have made it a better movie in fact. The casino planet is the most uninteresting planet that the Star Wars characters have ever explored.

13. The ATAT Walker scene with the resistance fighters evacuating at the end is the exact same as the Hoth scene from Empire Strikes Back.

14. Luke Skywalker would never go out intending to kill Ben Solo while he is asleep.

15. Apparently Rey\'s parents were junkies. What a story mark!

16. Luke doesn\'t die in battle but instead fades away when he actually wasn\'t even in the battle and in fact wasn\'t even tired. The "battle" wasn\'t even a battle anyway...

17. ... speaking of

there are no real lightsaber fights. First time ever in a main storyline star wars movie.

18. No appropriate send-off or conclusion for Leia/Carrie Fisher. '
